More Than Half of China’s Population to Live in Cities by 2015

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-24T06:16:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/more-than-half-of-china-s-population-to-live-in-cities-by-2015.html
More than half of  China ’s
population will live in cities by the end of 2015, the official
Xinhua News Agency reported, citing Xie Zhenhua, vice chairman
of the National Development and Reform Commission.  China’s so-called urbanization rate will rise to more than
51 percent from 47.5 percent at the end of 2010, according to
the report.  Also by 2015, China will cut carbon dioxide emissions by 17
percent and energy use by 16 percent per unit of economic output
from 2010 levels, Xinhua said, also citing Xie. Energy from non-
fossil fuel sources will rise to 11.4 percent of total
consumption, it added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tighe at 
 ptighe@bloomberg.net  